# Draft:Timeline of the Philippine Super Liga

The Philippine Super Liga (PSL) lasted from 2013 to 2021 with numerous teams competing in the league at various points.

2013–2016: Constant changes
2013 Invitational Conference
The league launched with six teams competing in the women's division: the Cagayan Valley Lady Rising Suns, Cignal HD Spikers, PCSO Bingo Milyonaryo Puffins, Petron Blaze Spikers, PLDT myDSL Speed Boosters, and TMS–Philippine Army Lady Troopers.

2013 Grand Prix Conference
The PSL established the men's division in this conference with four entrants: the Giligan's Sisig Kings, Maybank Tigers, PLDT myDSL Speed Boosters, and Systema Active Smashers.
Meanwhile in the women's division, only the PCSO Bingo Milyonaryo Puffins, with debutant RC Cola Raiders taking its place.

2014 All-Filipino Conference
The league saw the AirAsia Flying Spikers join the women's division while three teams joined the men's division: Cignal HD Spikers, Instituto Estetico Manila Phoenix Volley Masters, and Via Mare Voyagers.
Two teams departed on the men's side, those being the Giligan's Sisig Kings and Maybank Tigers.
Additionally, both PLDT teams were renamed to the PLDT Home TVolution Power Attackers. The Philippine Air Force also joined in, sponsoring the RC Cola Raiders and PLDT Home TVolution Power Attackers in the women's and men's divisions, respectively. Generika also sponsored the Philippine Army Lady Troopers thus becoming the Generika–Army Lady Troopers for this conference.

2014 Grand Prix Conference
Four teams departed from the women's division: AirAsia, Cagayan Valley, Generika–Army, and PLDT. Generika would establish its own team, the Generika Lifesavers, joining two other expansion teams: the Foton Tornadoes and the first incarnation of the Mane 'n Tail Lady Stallions.
The Fourbees Cavite Patriots Total Attackers are the only new team in the men's department and joined alongside the returning Maybank Tigers.
IEM and Via Mare both departed after one conference. Two teams on the men's side were also renamed with PLDT–Air Force becoming the PLDT Home Telpad–Air Force Turbo Boosters and Systema gaining the sponsorship of Bench, becoming the Bench–Systema Active Smashers.
After this conference, all men's teams except Maybank moved to Spikers' Turf.

2015 All-Filipino Conference
Following the establishment of Spikers' Turf, the men's division was dissolved with no remaining men's teams competing.
The women's division saw two departures in Generika and RC Cola–Air Force. The Shopinas.com Lady Clickers made their debut while the Mane 'n Tail Lady Stallions relaunched as a new team, with the former team becoming the Philips Gold Lady Slammers.

2016 Invitational Cup
Two teams debuted: the F2 Logistics Cargo Movers and New San Jose Builders Victorias. Meralco and Philips Gold departed as did RC Cola–Air Force. RC Cola would instead partner with the returning Philippine Army Lady Troopers, thus forming the RC Cola–Army Troopers.
Two teams changed names with Foton and Petron becoming the Foton Toplanders and Petron Tri-Activ Spikers, respectively.

2017–2020: Better turnout
2017 Invitational Cup
The Cocolife Asset Managers and Sta. Lucia Lady Realtors joined the league as F2 Logistics Cargo Movers and RC Cola–Army Troopers departed.
Petron reverted back to Petron Blaze Spikers while Generika's team gained a partnership with Ayala Corporation becoming the Generika–Ayala Lifesavers.

2020 and 2021 seasons
The Foton Tornadoes Blue Energy changed its name to Chery Tiggo Crossovers.}} The 2020 season and its Grand Prix Conference was the last for its indoor volleyball tournaments.
The following 2021 season was the last for the PSL before its dissolution following that year's Beach Volleyball Challenge Cup. Only Chery Tiggo (playing as United Auctioneers), F2 Logistics, and Sta. Lucia took part in the tournament. After the tournament, Chery Tiggo, Cignal, F2 Logistics, PLDT, and Sta. Lucia moved to the professional Premier Volleyball League. Generika–Ayala and Marinerang Pilipina would no longer compete afterwards.
